-- European Stocks Extend Drop as U.S. Consumer Confidence Falls in September
-- B y   D a v i d   M e r r i t t
-- 2010-09-28T14:03:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/european-stocks-extend-drop-as-u-s-consumer-confidence-falls-in-september.html
 European stocks extended declines
after a report showed confidence among U.S. consumers fell in
September to the lowest level in seven months as Americans
became more pessimistic about the labor market.  The benchmark Stoxx Europe 600 Index fell 1.1 percent to
260.11 at 3:02 p.m. in London.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Merritt at 
 dmerritt1@bloomberg.net  